<http://jsbin.com/zataqiqini/1/edit?js,console>

The extra parens wrapping the _function definition_ and then `()` at the end is just a little :javascript: trick to both define and invoke a function in one go. I just wrote it that way so that you can see the “scope structure”. You can ignore that aspect of the syntax though.
```
(function someName(){
  ...
})()
```
